[Kazekage Rescue Mission] {{main|Kazekage Rescue Mission}}
Angered that the Akatsuki had claimed Gaara's life, Naruto vowed to avenge his friend and fought the Akatsuki member Deidara. While under the influence of the Nine-Tails' chakra, Naruto ruthlessly pummeled and drove his Rasengan into Deidara, only to discover that he was fighting a clay clone. Growing frustrated, Naruto drew out more of the Nine-Tails' chakra, causing him to slip into his one-tailed form. Just as the second tail began to form, Kakashi immediately placed Jiraiya's special seal tag on Naruto's forehead, restoring him back to normal.
[Tenchi Bridge Reconnaissance Mission] {{main|Tenchi Bridge Reconnaissance Mission}}
At the Tenchi Bridge, where Team Yamato was facing Orochimaru and Kabuto, Naruto, enraged by Orochimaru's remark about Sasuke, attacked him in his three-tailed form. Naruto's rage intensified to the point where he gave into the Nine-Tails' influence, destroying the Tenchi Bridge and advancing into his four-tailed form while fighting Orochimaru. Unable to tell friend from foe, Naruto attacked anyone around him, including Sakura. After Yamato managed to suppress the Nine-Tails' chakra, he later revealed to Naruto that he was the one responsible for Sakura's injury, which greatly horrified Naruto and resolved to never rely on the Nine-Tails' power again.
thumb|left|The Nine-Tails tempts Naruto.
Soon afterwards, when Naruto encountered Sasuke again for the first time in almost three years, the Nine-Tails took it as an opportunity to tempt Naruto to release the seal. Naruto firmly refused, but the Nine-Tails scoffed, cruelly remarking that he couldn't do anything on his own. Before their quarrel could escalate any further, both Naruto and the Nine-Tails were shocked to see Sasuke suddenly appearing in Naruto's subconscious with his Sharingan. When the fox noted his similarity to Madara Uchiha in terms of visual prowess and chakra, Sasuke immediately responded by suppressing the fox. Although outraged by the display of his power, the Nine-Tails warned Sasuke not to kill Naruto, stating he would only regret it.
