[Akatsuki Suppression Mission] {{main|Akatsuki Suppression Mission}}
During Naruto's nature transformation training, the Nine-Tails' chakra began to surface within some of his shadow clones that had grown increasingly frustrated with the seemingly impossible task of combining the Rasengan with his wind element. Yamato was able to suppress the fox's chakra before it could do serious damage.
[Pain's Assault] {{main|Pain's Assault (Arc)|l1=Pain's Assault}}
At Mount Myōboku, Naruto trained with the elder toad sage Fukasaku in the art of senjutsu. Once Naruto attained a perfected Sage Mode, the Nine-Tails, out of anger and jealousy, continuously rejected Fukasaku's attempts to fuse with Naruto in order to help mold the senjutsu chakra for him, which forced Naruto to look for other alternatives to overcome this disadvantage.
thumb|Naruto's eight-tailed form breaks through Pain's Chibaku Tensei.
Later, during Naruto's battle with Pain, he slipped into his six-tailed form right after Pain appeared to have killed Hinata Hyūga. Despite the necklace's attempts to suppress it, the Nine-Tails quickly seized the necklace and crushed it. When Naruto was soon contained by Pain's Chibaku Tensei technique, the Nine-Tails tempted Naruto to entrust his heart to it so that it could destroy everything that was causing Naruto pain, thus distorting the seal to the point where the eight-tailed form was released. Before it could convince him to completely remove the seal, the spirit of Minato appeared in Naruto's subconscious and stopped him. Enraged, the Nine-Tails tried to dare Minato to come closer so it could rip him to shreds, but Minato simply ignored it and restored the seal to its original strength.
